    "Hersey began teaching at Yale in 1963 and published his first book, <em>Alfonso II and the Artistic Renewal of Naples, 1485-95</em>, in 1969.": [],
    "He became a full professor in the Department of the History of Art in 1971.": [],
    "In the same year he was appointed editor of Yale Publications on the History of Art, a position he held for almost two decades.": [],
    "In 1972, he published his doctoral research under the title <em>High Victorian Gothic: A Study in Associationism</em>.": [],
    "Hersey followed this with three works on the architecture of the Italian Renaissance: The Aragonese Arch at Naples, 1443-1477 (1973), <em>Pythagorean Palaces: Architecture and Magic in the Italian Renaissance</em> (1976), and <em>Architecture, Poetry, and Number in the Royal Palace at Caserta</em> (1983), the latter being the first book in English about Luigi Vanvitelli\u2019s (1700-1773) Neapolitan masterpiece.": [
